**What happens if X chooses a corner or side instead**

- A corner move gives X only three lines (row, column, one diagonal). O can then play the opposite corner and create a fork, forcing X into a defensive position.
- A side move gives X only two lines, and O can immediately take the center, gaining the advantage.

