You are **O** and it is your turn.  
With X already in the centre, the only way for you to force a win is to create a *fork* (two non‑blocking lines that give you two simultaneous winning chances).  
A single O cannot fork on the first move, but the position you choose will determine how many fork opportunities you can create on your next turn and how many you must block.

**Why a corner is best**

* A corner gives you the most potential lines: it is part of two diagonals, one row, and one column.  
* If you play a corner, X cannot block all of your future fork possibilities in one move.  
* Any edge move (middle of a side) gives X a single reply that can block all of your future forks, because an edge belongs to only one row/column and one diagonal.

**What X can do after a corner**

If you play (0,0), X’s best reply is to take the opposite corner (2,2) or any other corner.  
